.TH "__ipi_send_single" 9 "__ipi_send_single" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__ipi_send_single \- send an IPI to a target Linux SMP CPU
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __ipi_send_single
.BI "(struct irq_desc *desc "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "desc" 12
pointer to irq_desc of the IRQ
.IP "cpu" 12
destination CPU, must in the destination mask passed to
\fBirq_reserve_ipi\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is for architecture or core code to speed up IPI sending. Not
usable from driver code.

Returns zero on success and negative error number on failure.
